<SLUG> BC-BBO-RANGERS-WILLIAMS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RANGERS ACQUIRE RICKY WILLIAMS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOHNNY PAUL 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ The Rangers took a $100,000 gamble yesterday
that the nation's premier college football player will develop his
crude baseball skills in their minor-league system.
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers purchased the contract of Heisman Trophy
winner/minor-league outfielder Ricky Williams from the Montreal
Expos for $100,000 and risked surrendering infielder Scott Sheldon
by designating him for assignment.
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers placed Sheldon on outright waivers for the purpose
of assigning him to Triple-A Oklahoma of the Pacific Coast League.
Sheldon, who hit .256 with 29 home runs and 96 runs batted in this
season for the RedHawks, must clear waivers to remain with the
organization. Sheldon will go to spring training with the Rangers
and compete for a berth on the Opening Day roster as a reserve
should he clear waivers.
</P>
<P>
   Williams, who has never played above Class A, must spend an
entire season on the Rangers' 25-man roster or be offered to the
Philadelphia Phillies for $25,000. The Expos chose Williams from
the Phillies' Scranton/Wilkes-Barre roster for $50,000 with the
fifth selection in the Rule V Draft on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ``The object is to try and get him in our minor-league system,''
Rangers general manager Doug Melvin said of Williams, who will be
invited to major-league camp as a memeber of the Rangers' 40-man
roster. ``That's sort of the purpose of this. This is Step 1 at
this time. We'll worry about the rest down the road.''
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers could place Williams on the suspended list should he
decide to play football professionally, but it would not subtract
from the time he must spend on the 25-man roster.
</P>
<P>
   The other option would be to designate Williams for assignment
after spring training and hope he clears waivers.
</P>
<P>
   Williams spent the four summers playing in the Phillies'
minor-league system and hit .211 with four home runs and 46 stolen
bases in 565 at-bats.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-16-98 0130EST &QL; 
