<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ While House members pondered impeachment,
they were being subjected to heavy pressure by their congressional
leadership and the White House. In civilian life, this would be
known as jury tampering, and subject to strict handling by the
courts. (Rosenfeld, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Join John Kelso's Extremely
Stupid Christmas Card Contest. If you have a Christmas card that is
anywhere near as silly as this one _ Robert Burns, the art director
of the '70s cult horror classic ``The Texas Chainsaw Massacre''
standing next to the famous Seguin, Texas cement pecan _ please
send a copy of it to me at this newspaper, P.O. Box 670, Austin, TX
78767, and you could become famous. (Kelso, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ President Richard Milhous Nixon
was standing a few feet in front of me, sweating and twitching, on
Sunday evening, Nov. 11, 1973. ``People have got to know whether or
not their president is a crook,'' he said. ``Well, I'm not a
crook.'' Nixon, unlike President William Jefferson Clinton, was a
lousy liar. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
