the carpets in Susan Jeffrey Lepper's house got dirty faster than
she could clean it. After a decade of calling in carpet cleaners
several times a year, the west Cobb resident decided to buy her own
carpet cleaner, a Hoover shampooer that she and her husband Reg can
use anytime, anywhere. Let's face it: If you've got carpeting,
you'll have to deal with cleaning it at some point beyond weekly
vacuuming. Some options. (Mowry, Atlanta Journal-Constitution
