<HEADER>
A2541 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-VIDEO-RDP17-COX     12-16 0361
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-RDP17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini reviews of movies released on video
 &HT;    By Eleanor Ringel and Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Halloween: H20'' (R) _ Jamie Lee Curtis returns in this
unsurprising 20th anniversary sequel to John Carpenter's 1978
frightfest ``Halloween.'' Now, she's a single mom to 17-year-old
John (Josh Hartnett). Also back is Michael Myers, the maniac who
stalked Curtis all those years ago. You can easily guess who'll
survive and who'll get cut out of the picture, literally. But when
Curtis pulls a Sigourney Weaver, a la ``Aliens,'' stalking Michael
instead of fleeing him, the movie finally gets some juice. Grade: C
+ST
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Hav Plenty'' (R) _ Plays like the first draft of what might
have been a good comedy. Writer-director-star Christopher Scott
Cherot is Lee Plenty. Dateless on New Year's Eve he happily accepts
an invitation to a party from his friend Havilland (Chenoa
Maxwell), whom he secretly adores. Cherot is a likable performer,
but he doesn't have the movie star wattage his role needs. Grade: C
ST
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``A Friend of the Deceased'' (R) _ In this bittersweet comedy
about life after Communism in Kiev, a frustrated translator
(Alexandre Lazarev) decides to hire a hitman on himself.
Complications arise when he changes his mind. A meandering but
engaging shaggy-dog story, told with an ironic, vodka-soaked
that's-how-it-is shrug. Grade: B ER
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Air Bud: Golden Receiver'' (G) _ If you're under 8, this
``Bud's'' for you. In this sequel to ``Air Bud,'' Buddy, the
hoop-shooting Golden Retriever, and his boy, Josh (Kevin Zegers)
trade basketball for football. Script-wise, it's little more than a
glorified after-school special, but there hasn't been much around
for younger kids recently and it handles its messages well. And so
what if the movie is essentially a series of Stupid Pet Tricks? In
his K-9 jersey, pads and helmet, Buddy looks more athletically
heroic than Bruce Willis. (In stores Friday.) Grade: B - ER
</P>
<P>
   Eleanor Ringel and Steve Murray write for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
