   MARKET (New York) _ At midday, the industrial average was down
41 points, or half a percent, and the Nasdaq index was little
changed. Elsewhere, prices rose 0.6 percent in Tokyo and fell 0.1
percent in Hong Kong. They were up 2.6 percent in Frankfurt, 0.9
percent in London. They were down 2.8 percent in Brazil and 0.7
percent in Mexico. On the American debt market, the long bond was
off 4/32 point, with the yield at 5.03 percent. By Robert D.
Hershey.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-GOLDMAN (Shanghai) _ Goldman, Sachs and the government of
Guangdong province will pump money into Guangdong Enterprises
Holdings, an investment firm owned by the province. Guangdong hires
Goldman to be the first foreign adviser to a Chinese provincial
government, and the American firm will spend as much as $20 million
to buy a stake in Guangdong Enterprises. The agreement is an
indication that China is willing to reach out to foreign expertise
to fix the problems plaguing its hundreds of foundering investment
trusts _ and is an indication of how eager foreign firms are to
cozy up to the Chinese government. By Seth Faison.
</P>
