businesses, slumped. But its shares rise 9 percent. By Dana Canedy.
</P>
<P>
   3M-OUTLOOK (Chicago) _ Minnesota Mining and Manufacturing says
per-share earnings in the current quarter will fall 10 percent
because of slower production, sales that are lower than expected
and the effect of currency translations. It plans to cut 2,000 jobs
by the end of this month as part of the 4,500 positions it
previously announced it would eliminate by the end of next year.
Its shares fall 5 percent. By David Barboza.
</P>
<P>
