<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AUDIO-RAP17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Rhymes hits new heights on ``Extinction''
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Extinction Level Event'' arrives with a maelstrom of hits.
Finally, Busta Rhymes' musical accompaniment not only matches his
vibrancy of as hip-hop's most animated rapper, but seems to
challenge him to do more than see how fast he can get to the end of
each line. With an eye to the Y2K, and his teeth clenched as
always, Rhymes eases forcefully through attacks on his
short-sighted peers (``Against All Odds'') and the material
pursuits of some women (``Just Give It To Me Raw''). Then he hits
hyperspeed: verbally, with the equally-as-kinetic rapper Mystikal
on ``Iz They Wildin Wit Us &AMP; Gettin Rowdy Wit Us?''; and
figuratively, on a sweaty team-up with a cooing Janet Jackson
(``What's It Gonna Be?!''). Listeners only have a few uneventful
tracks at the start of the album to secure themselves, and prepare
for the explosion to come.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ext
</P>
</TEXT>
