</P>
<P>
   SCI-CLONE (Seoul, South Korea) _ South Korean scientists said
Wednesday that they had cloned a human cell from an infertile
woman, creating an embryo that theoretically could have grown into
a physical replica of the woman. But they said that because of the
legal and ethical implications of their work, they stopped the
experiment and did not try to breed a human clone. By Sheryl
WuDunn.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
