<SLUG> BC-MEXICO-REPORTER-DEATH-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
REPORTER FOUND DEAD IN MEXICO 
</HEADLINE>
  (dal) 
 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY _ The body of Philip True, Mexico correspondent for
the San Antonio Express-News, was found Wednesday in a remote
ravine in western Mexico, 17 days after True hiked into the
mountains on a reporting trek, authorities said. True, who was 50,
apparently fell to his death.
</P>
<P>
   ``There has been no autopsy at this point, but it appears that
he died of a fall,'' said Steve Morrisseau, a U.S. embassy
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   The body was spotted Wednesday morning from a small plane, one
of several army aircraft sweeping the area, military officials told
The Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
   True, an experienced hiker, entered the mountains on the border
of the Jalisco and Nayarit states on Nov. 29 to photograph and
write about the region's Huichol Indians. He called family and
friends several times by telephone from villages along the way, but
the communication ended on Dec. 7. His family reported him missing
on Dec. 10.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
