<SLUG> BC-SOLSTICE-ATHEISTS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HAPPY SOLSTICE! ATHEIST TO PUT SIGN NEXT TO COURTHOUSE NATIVITY
SCENE 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By EVAN MOORE 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEATHERFORD, Texas _ The only recognized atheist in town has
scored a victory with an agreement that allows him to place a pagan
sign next to the Nativity scene in front of the county courthouse.
</P>
<P>
   Dick Hogan, a retiree in this town west of Fort Worth, is a
member and former state director of the American Atheists Inc., a
group founded by Madalyn Murray O'Hair prior to her disappearance
three years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Hogan sued Parker County two years ago over its display of the
Christmas manger scene.
</P>
<P>
   That lawsuit was settled recently with the stipulation that
Hogan be allowed to erect a sign beside the display, stating:
``Happy Winter Solstice, the REAL reason for the season!''
</P>
<P>
   The winter solstice marks the time when the sun travels in its
lowest arc across the horizon and results in the shortest day of
the year. It usually falls on Dec. 21 in the Northern Hemisphere.
</P>
<P>
   The sign refers to a ritual staged by some ancient religions to
honor sun gods and encourage the sun to return and warm the Earth.
</P>
<P>
   Hogan plans to put up the sign Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ``Then I guess we'll see how long it stays up there,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   The county was joined by the Young Business Leaders of Parker
County in efforts to fend off the atheist's lawsuit, which was
filed in federal district court in Fort Worth. &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; The three parties met in an open forum recently and the county
consented to Hogan's sign.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not something I necessarily agreed with personally and I
expect there will be some folks highly offended by this,'' said
Parker County Judge Dan Long.
</P>
<P>
   ``However, I agreed to uphold the law when I took this position
and he had the law on his side.''
</P>
<P>
   Hogan said he knows of one other supporter in the largely
Christian county, ``but I'm the only one who's out of the closet,
so to speak.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
