NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, DECEMBER 17
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-IMPEACH-BOEHLERT-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Dec. 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Dec. 15,
about Representative Sherwood L. Boehlert, a Republican from
central New York's 23d Congressional District, and his position on
impeachment, misstated the district's Presidential vote in 1992. It
was 40 percent for George Bush; Bill Clinton got 37.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-DRUG-TESTING-NYT (moved on Monday, Nov. 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Nov. 16,
about drug testing kits associated one substance incorrectly with
QuickScreen at Home, a test made by Phamatech. A telephone call
from the company on Monday said that QuickScreen checks for
marijuana, cocaine and heroin but not LSD.
</P>
<P>
   BC-NABISCO-CUTBACKS-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 14)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Dec. 14,
about cutbacks announced by RJR Nabisco Holdings referred
incorrectly to a decision on plant closings at its food subsidiary,
Nabisco Holdings. The company has indeed decided which plants will
close, but has not identified them publicly.
</P>
