 This ``separate buy'' article is from Latin Trade magazine,
America's leading journal of Latin American business, finance and
trade: &HT;    NAFTA: EXPANDING HORIZONS. NAFTA has been a positive addition
for U.S. and Canadian multinationals and those companies looking
for export markets where rules were clear and fair. But for Mexican
companies _ and especially the country's largest firms _ the trade
agreement has been nothing short of a clarion call to shape up in
order to compete in the global economy.
 &HT;    Filed as BC-NAFTA:IMPETUS-LATINTRADE-NYTSF.
