<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONS-PROBOWL17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    5 Falcons in Pro Bowl, but not Archambeau
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Five Atlanta Falcons made the NFC's Pro Bowl roster
Wednesday, as middle linebacker Jessie Tuggle, free safety Eugene
Robinson, cornerback Ray Buchanan and running back Jamal Anderson
got starting nods. Quarterback Chris Chandler will be a reserve.
</P>
<P>
   It will be the fifth Pro Bowl for Tuggle, 33, the third for
Robinson, 35, the second for Chandler, 33, and the first for
Buchanan, 27, and Anderson, 26.
</P>
<P>
   Chandler, whose 96.2 passer rating is fourth-highest in the NFL,
has completed 176 of 305 passes (57.7 percent) for a career-high
2,890 yards and a Falcons-record 21 touchdowns with 12
interceptions.
</P>
<P>
   ``It says a lot about the Falcons, and the recognition we've
gotten. I think we can look at it and feel like there should be
more (Falcons),'' said Chandler, who last year went to the game as
an alternate.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's very satisfying personally, especially in this
conference, when you have Brett Favre and Troy Aikman, and they're
playing well. It's kind of a reward for two years.''
</P>
<P>
   Defensive end Chuck Smith and left tackle Bob Whitfield are
first alternates, but the most glaring omission was left defensive
end Lester Archambeau, who was not listed among the first four
alternates at his position.
</P>
<P>
   Archambeau is fourth on the team with 74 tackles on a defense
that is ranked No. 7 overall in the NFL and No. 2 against the run.
</P>
<P>
   ``You look at the numbers ... and for Lester Archambeau to not
even get mentioned is a crying shame. It's ridiculous, really,''
said Rich Brooks, interim head coach and defensive coordinator.
``He's got (a team- and carer-high) 10 sacks, following 8.5 last
year, he's caused (a team- and career-high) seven fumbles. ... All
he does is play at a Pro Bowl level.''
</P>
<P>
   Tuggle, who has led the team in tackles nine years in a row, is
tied with linebacker Cornelius Bennett, a third alternate, for the
team lead with 105. He made Pro Bowls in 1992, '94, '95 and '97.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson is third with 81 tackles, has three interceptions, one
returned for a touchdown, two fumbles forced and one recovered. He
made the AFC team while playing for Seattle in '92 and '93.
</P>
<P>
   Buchanan leads the NFC with seven interceptions, has 53 tackles
and has broken up a team-high 15 passes.
</P>
<P>
   Anderson is second in the NFL with 1,596 rushing yards, has a
franchise-record 10 games with 100 or more rushing yards, and is on
pace to carry the ball 414 times, which would be an NFL record. He
also has scored 13 touchdowns, second in the NFC.
</P>
<P>
   Pro Bowl voting is done by players, fans and coaches, each
counting one-third.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
