   (NYT17) NEW YORK -- Dec. 16, 1998 -- VINOLY-DESIGN-2, 12-16 --
Roman Vinoly, left, and his brother Lucas, sit next to their
mother, Diana, in their apartment, which she decorated. Ms. Vinoly,
a designer, drew on the classic silhouettes of some modern
furniture designs, a testament to beauty in brevity, and revived an
old standby: the built-in wall unit. (Fred R. Conrad/New York Times
Photo)
